The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, held a daily press briefing on September 3, 2015. During the briefing, he discussed several topics including the refugee crisis, the Iran nuclear deal, Russia's involvement in Syria, and the resignation of Guatemalan President Otto Perez Molina. Earnest also mentioned the President's focus on expanding economic opportunity for the middle class and the importance of a strong SEC commissioner. He declined to comment on the possibility of the President endorsing a candidate in the Democratic Primary.